  <span id="freeText13744506506351927926" style="display:none">3.5 Better than the first. However, there were still a lot of problems. Questions weren't asked that even a passable cop would. It made Mercy and Truman appear incompetent at times. Ben the cop, I think his name was, walked into danger so easily after cops had been shot the night before. It was so obvious. Are the cops in that town that stupid? Kade thinks there are illegal activities and he goes there alone. Another stupid move. All of these were written to further the plot but come off as amateur crime writing. Better reasons for the characters actions could have been thought of. Plus Mercy never challenges her dad. She continues allowing this men elitist mentality. She lost points with me. Otherwise a decent read.</span>
