<span id="freeTextContainer15728510675958737042">2.75 stars.<br/><br/>The relationship that Mercy had with some of her family was downright depressing, but the rest of this story was enjoyable. From the mystery to the tender romance between the MCs, I liked this quite a bit. The mystery wasn&apos;t all that mysterious necessarily, but it was interesting nonetheless. Even though the whole prepper/anti-Big Brother/free man society isn&apos;t my favourite theme, I&apos;m looking forward to continuing on with this series. </span>
  <span id="freeText15728510675958737042" style="display:none">2.75 stars.<br /><br />The relationship that Mercy had with some of her family was downright depressing, but the rest of this story was enjoyable. From the mystery to the tender romance between the MCs, I liked this quite a bit. The mystery wasn't all that mysterious necessarily, but it was interesting nonetheless. Even though the whole prepper/anti-Big Brother/free man society isn't my favourite theme, I'm looking forward to continuing on with this series. </span>
