        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2424528376" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9392811626801734591">This is the second book in this series and I did not enjoy it nearly as much as the first novel. This one tends to drift into being over sentimental and quite corny in parts. It reached the point that if I read the phrase &apos;it warmed her heart&apos; one more time I was going to scream.<br/>Once again the story is set in central Oregan in a remote township surrounded by &apos;preppers&apos;. Someone is setting fires and when two police officers are shot at the scene the FBI become involved. Mercy Kilpatrick is grew u</span>
  <span id="freeText9392811626801734591" style="display:none">This is the second book in this series and I did not enjoy it nearly as much as the first novel. This one tends to drift into being over sentimental and quite corny in parts. It reached the point that if I read the phrase 'it warmed her heart' one more time I was going to scream.<br />Once again the story is set in central Oregan in a remote township surrounded by 'preppers'. Someone is setting fires and when two police officers are shot at the scene the FBI become involved. Mercy Kilpatrick is grew up in the area and knows the town and its people. How involved is her estranged family in this latest issue?</span>
  <a data-text-id="9392811626801734591" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
